name: Starbucks Coffee
directions: Straight back.
comment: Staff are friendly.

name: The LGBT Center of Las Vegas
directions: Enter through the front and the bathrooms are straight forward on the right hand side.
comment: Best and safest gender neutral and gender non conforming bathrooms in Las Vegas!

name: Cabela's
directions: Go through the front doors, bathrooms are on the right before entering the main store. The unisex bathroom is located between the men's and women's bathrooms.
comment: It a sporting goods store with a clothing section, you can pop in and walk through for a second or two and say "you didn't have what I needed" but it's an upscale suburb of Portland I doubt they really care.

name: East Shore Unitarian Church
directions: In administration building, up indoor ramp on left side of building, in back corner.
comment: Let anyone who asks know that you're looking for the gender neutral (single stall) bathroom.  East Shore is a welcoming community and is LGBTQ friendly.

name: Haggen Food and Pharmacy
directions: Family Restroom, accessible equipped, by the larger gendered restrooms. Near the pharmacy department.

name: Switzerland Cafe
directions: Main floor in Cafe

name: Kashi Atlanta
directions: 2 unisex bathrooms opposite the front desk; 1 unisex bathroom downstairs. Wheelchair access through the side entrance off Nelms Ave.
comment: Everyone is welcome at Kashi. Let the front desk staff know you are in need of a safe restroom.

name: A Natural Path
directions: Front of the building- doctors office, but you are still welcome.
comment: You are welcome

name: AIDS Care Service
directions: End suite in brick building with red awnings
comment: Office hours Mon-Fri 9am to 5pm

name: Mystery Brewing Public House
directions: Back of the pub, next to door to the patio
comment: Owners are LGBTQ friendly

name: Bluestone Lane Collective Cafe
directions: In back marked "Loo".
comment: Paying customers only. Pretty narrow and inaccessible. Single stall with lock.

name: Anderson Academic Commons
directions: There are several single-stall bathrooms, all of which lock. All of them are on the northeast side of the building, and there is one on each floor.

name: Alamo Drafthouse Cinema Lakeline
comment: Large single-stall labelled “F” for family use. Visible from the main entryway, toward the back. At least will be useful when leaving a late-night show and the theater isn’t crowded.

name: Genuine Joe Coffeehouse
directions: Two gender-neutral single-stall bathrooms. They are explicitly labelled as such, friendly atmosphere.

name: Insomnia Cookies
comment: Prolly buy a cookie if you can. Open til 3 am

name: Caffé nero
directions: The very back of the café, on the right hand side.

name: McDonalds
directions: It's just opposite the checkout, to the right of the ketchup & napkin stand
comment: You might have to buy something? Although, you could probably get away with just going in to use the bathroom and walking out.

name: Taqueria de los Muertos
comment: Buy something at counter first

name: Potbelly Sandwich Shop
directions: As soon as one enters turn to the left.
comment: It's pretty crowded so one can sneak in; otherwise paying costumers only.

name: 220 E Roosevelt St, Phoenix, AZ 85004, USA
directions: Walk toward the art in the back and look to your right

name: Vegele
directions: From entrance: take double doors on the right into the Ökotussi shop. Keep going left until you find the bathroom door.
comment: You will probably have to be a paying customer, and if the double doors are locked, just ask staff about the bathroom.

name: Tacorinos
directions: Go straight after entering.
comment: Owner is really nice I'm sure one can go in without buying.

name: Commons Drive [P], Oxford, PA 19363, USA
directions: On the back of the store behind the hardware department is a family restroofm

name: Södertörns University
directions: Toilets on every floor. Near each building wing and near the elevator.
comment: They are free and every toilet is gender neutral. Accessible toilets are few and spread across the buildings. There is one near then Cafe Arom.

name: Student Union
directions: Through the main entrance by the bookstore. Left past the welcome desk, down the hall a bit and on your right. Should be bewteen the gendered bathrooms.
comment: Should have a sign stating it is safe for use by all genders and expressions.

name: Peck Hall
directions: There are gender neutral bathrooms on each floor. I know there is one immediately through the door on the red stairwell, opposite of the pod.
comment: All neutral bathroom have been remarked as safe for use by all genders and expressions.

name: Berea Coffee and Tea
directions: Enter (if in front, there's a sign, if in back, it is right next to the fudge shoppe. It's confusing, so you may have to ask someone). Near the back, there are two gendered single stalls, the female being on the hall towards the nack door, and the male being in the back left corner of the dining area.
comment: Not unisex, but an accepting establishment and you don't have to worry about being judged: people use both of them a lot if someone is taking too long.

name: Union Church of Christ
directions: Go into the parking lot in the back. Go up stairs (next to long handicap ramp. When you enter, go up the tiny flight of stairs to the next level. There is a one stall bathroom in here.
comment:
1. If the bathroom is taken, go to the office (to the left of the bathroom) and ask about other locations for the bathrooms. We are an accepting church and will help you out.
2. The church may mot be open on some days.

name: University of Victoria Student Union Building
directions: In the middle of the building, next to the UVSS Info Booth.
comment: There are two gender-neutral multi-stall bathrooms. They were formerly gendered, so I believe one has urinals, but both are open to anyone. You do not have to be a student to use them.

name: Hamilton train station
directions: Platform 2, single stall

name: Bealls Outlet
directions: Directly across the store in the middle. Right of Guest Services, in the Home Section
comment: You do not need to be a paying customer. It is a single-stall duel-sex restroom. The fitting rooms are also all neutral :D

name: Australian Bakery
directions: Straight back.

name: University of New Haven
directions: Two single stall gender neutral bathrooms in Bayer Hall. You should be able to see them to your left and right slightly towards the back of the room. If you have trouble finding them, ask the person at the front desk.
comment: I believe this is only open Monday through Friday.

name: Malarkey Pool Hall
directions: They have a womens & men's restroom. Inside the men's restroom are 2 single stalls & 2 urinals.  There is a also a handicap restroom.  All are located towards the middle of the pool hall on the left.
comment: 21 & up establishment

name: Cheba Hut "Toasted" Subs
directions: Single stall, ask for key, must be a customer

name: The Wok Express
directions: The restrooms are in the back of the restaurant. Upon entering, stay to the right and walk all the way back until you almost enter the kitchen.
comment: There are two gendered single stall bathrooms.

name: Vanderbilt University
directions: Ground floor to the left
comment: There are two, both accessible and both gender neutral.

name: al ain
directions: Lllll
comment: Hi

name: al ain
directions: Lllll
comment: Hi

name: Starbucks
directions: Under the chandelier, near one of the entrances.
comment: You are supposed to be a paying customer. There are multiple gender neutral locking single stalls here. Note that the sink and mirrors are outside of the stalls, not in the stall itself.

name: Sabor Y Cultura
directions: In the back, at the end of the hallway, by the parking lot door.
comment: You have to get a key from the cafe cashier.

name: Lost n Found
directions: by the dressing rooms

name: UCC Students' Union Common Room
comment: Better look like a student, I guess

name: Kreutzplatz Puplic Toilett
directions: Behind the Kiosk by the Tramstation

name: Sparsholt college
directions: At the equine centre; by Student Services; in MJ's social centre; other

name: 234-236 N 1st St W, Missoula, MT 59802, USA
comment: Art gallery, all ages music venue.

name: Washington State University Tri-cities
directions: There is more than one stall so you can lock the door when in use.

name: Star Lounge Coffee Bar
directions: Two on main floor near register area.

name: West Building, 2700 Crimson Way, Richland, WA 99354, USA
comment: lock the door when in use.

name: Markin Family Student Recreation Center
directions: When you enter on the East side, it is immediately to the left, near the pool window. It's a Family changing room with a restroom attached.

name: Yoshi's Restaurant
directions: East side of restaurant, requires key from front counter

name: Westlake Hall(Bradley University)
directions: On the southern end of older part of the building on any of the floors there should be a pair of gendered but single stall restrooms side by side.

name: Simmons College
directions: Basement of MCB, past the Fens Lobby by the Bookstore

name: Centennial Hall
directions: Each of the four floors has a gender-inclusive restroom, located around the corner from the binary restrooms, near the elevators.

name: Nekocards
street: Nekocards, Little Lonsdale Street, Melbourne, Victoria, Australia
directions: Little Lonsdale off Elizabeth. Go up the stairs to Nekocards and the bathroom is to the right of the counter.
comment: They're usually quite busy so don't mind if you don't buy anything, and the staff are friendly.

name: Boyer Center for Molecular Medicine
directions: On the first floor, there's one as soon as you walk in, to your right. There's another on the third floor, go up stairs or elevator and turn away from the labs. There's a little hallway that will take you into Hope and it's in your left as soon as you go through the set of doors.
comment: You do need a Yale ID to enter but you can usually piggyback onto the person going in in front of you.

name: Williams Hall(Bradley Hall)
directions: Two gendered single stall bathrooms are in the lobby.
comment: Some work is being done to make these gender neutral but has not yet been made official.

name: Pizza Hut
directions: Immediately to your right when you enter.

name: University Hall(Bradley University
directions: The family bathroom is in the lobby.
comment: It may be difficult to access the building if you do not live there.

name: Uptown Espresso
directions: To the far right of the cafe, labeled "Restroom"

name: Florida Citrus Center Inc
directions: In the back by the gendered restrooms.
comment: Don't have to buy anything, you can walk right in. Single stall.

name: Bibliotheca Albertina
directions: From main entrance: directly left. There is another set of restrooms on the floor above.

name: Veganz Leipzig
directions: From the entrance: far back-right corner of the shop.

name: Super Target
directions: Unisex restroom by the pharmacy, or there's a family restroom in the front

name: Washington State University, Vancouver
directions: Inside the Plant Building

name: Washington State University, Vancouver
directions: Ground floor of the Undergraduate Building

name: Kaiser Permanent Clovis
directions: Head straight through the main (west-facing) entrance to the back. The restrooms are in the Laboratory/Radiology Department
comment: It's a big building and usually pretty busy, so no need to worry about acting like a customer no one will notice.

name: Safeway
directions: To the left of the customer service counter.
comment: Narrow doorway may make it a tight squeeze for wheelchair users.

name: McDonald's
directions: First thing you see when you walk in the entrance on the right
comment: A spacey single stalled bathroom that is wheelchair accessible.

name: Bennu café
directions: First floor near the back before the stairs.

name: Bar Ampre
directions: Walk to the back of this small bar, bathrooms on the right. Nice ones too :-)
comment: 2 x individual non gendered bathrooms in a small quiet bar, almost always vacant. Walk straight in, should be all good.

name: Anytime Fitness
directions: Through the front doors and straight to the back of the gym, just past all the weight equipment
comment: Have to be a gym member, unfortunately

name: Foy
directions: Second floor by women's restroom

name: Soho Park 62 Prince St, New York, NY 10012, USA
directions: On your left when you enter.
comment: Preferably a paid customer.

name: Amerikick
directions: Enter in through the front door, make your way around the karate mat where people are most likely working out, and head to the bathroom and the left next to the office.

name: 7 Griffiths Ct, Dandenong North VIC 3175, Australia
Kohl's
directions: In the back of the store  by customers service
comment: Family restroom

name: Value Village

comment: There's a buzzer next to the door that you have to press to get the door unlocked.

name: Lasalle's cafe
directions: Back hallway, take a left at the pizza counter
comment: You should be a paying customer, at least they are relatively inexpensive.

name: Kohls
directions: Upstairs (there is an elevator), to the left of the service desk with the other bathrooms

name: Lucky Horseshoe
directions: Go through the left door on the back wall. It is a small bar.

directions: In pharmacy area, next to vitamins
